<br>
1.) Pet is very nice sustained DPS (comparable to a non-casting hybrid or lower end tank in most cases - ie. decent by itself.)  Even when mage is OOM, Jobabtik is still out there doing damage.<br>
<br>
2.) Useful summons, including focus items that boost buff durations (hello!  save me mana rebuffing and Dot costs!) and damage for the wizzies (/hug bracelet, earring, ring)<br>
<br>
3.) Useful debuffs on the mob (/hug malo line)<br>
<br>
4.) Nice unresistable damage vs. non-slowed mobs via damage shields (believe it or not, there are times when NOT having a slower works...)<br>
<br>
5.) Very nice nuking DPS when they open up the mana hose, better short term DPS than rogues for when adds come in and its necessary to melt them down fast.<br>
<br>
Let me assure any mages on the Saryrn server that if you need a cleric for your group to look me up!  I love grouping with yall!<br>
<br>
(edit: forgot no aggro from healing pets, and modrods for emergencies, and...well, mages rock!) <p>Zarros Livinglight<br>
Templar of Tunare<br>
Wings of the Chimera<br>
Saryrn<br>
