<br>
I will emphasize as others have that building groups is the key.  Yesterday as an example, I zoned into PoI, and found an enchanter <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>/LFG ON</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and invited them.  Now I have a slower, which is the core of a PoP group, and we started exping immediately while recruiting.  Over time, while killing mobs, we recruited another mage, then a druid, then a necromancer, later on a bard.  With three strong pets, we killed mobs very quickly, even the unslowable ones.  No wipeouts, no deaths, and it all went very smoothly.<br>
<br>
Having a good reputation helps you both recruit others and be recruited.  I have been building groups for most of my career.  Prior to 61, I was especially good at finding odd corners to pull and built groups there, so I met a lot of people.  I also am an adequate puller, and the horse helps enormously in some places.  I am known for getting small groups together and going quickly, and for sustaining those groups as the membership shifts.  I am attentive to details, and make sure everyone has rods, focii, arrows, whatever.<br>
<br>
Thus more often than not, I need only <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>/LFG ON</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> at the beginning of my session, and while I am still summoning I get tells either inviting me, or asking if I am starting a group.<br>
<br>
With all respect, I do think that an openly negative attitude towards mages is going to impact how often one is invited to groups.  I for one would prefer not to group with someone who repeatedly gripes about their class and their lack of abilities.  I would much prefer to group with someone who uses their skills in a workmanlike manner to advance the group to the best of their abilities.<br>
<br>
Two more comments.  I like the new <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Rthen</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> if this is an example.  Concrete examples, explicit reasoning, and no implicit condemnation of others.  You would also do well to re-consider your foreswearing of serial pet reclamation.  Using <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Reclaim Energy</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to gain mana is a powerful technique, and you will have much less down time if you take advantage of it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
