<br>
Lower level players:<br>
1) Bring most of the abilities of their higher level companions.<br>
2) Are pleased to have a group in a higher level zone.<br>
3) Are easier to control and lead.<br>
4) Remember you well later.<br>
<br>
Having <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">a</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> slower is so much better than having <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">no</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> slower, etc.  I would really rather get the ball moving as soon as possible as opposed to waiting for some ideal group or camp that may never happen, or which may break up.<br>
<br>
I am doing well with pet groups and recommend them highly.<br>
<br>
